  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Global (Burkina Faso and the Philippines): Advancing Women&apos;s and Girls&apos; Action for Climate Justice through the Rule of Law</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To improve capacity of state institutions and other key stakeholders to ensure gender-transformative climate laws, policies and action. 2) To increase understanding of women leaders and women organizations of environmental rights and the processes to claim them. 3) To strengthen the evidence base on rule of law approaches to address the impacts of climate change on women and girls. 4) To improve integration of gender-transformative approaches to climate justice in global policy dialogues.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to strengthen the ability of women and girls to promote and protect their environmental rights and shape climate action through the rule of law.</narrative>
  </description>
